Type
public class ComplexType
extends Component
implements Type

Encapsulates a complex type definition. A complex type definition is either

  • a restriction of a complex base type definition;
  • an extenstion of a simple or complex base type definition
  • a restriction of the ur-type definition (default)

    Constructor Detail

    ComplexType

    public ComplexType(java.lang.String name,
                   java.lang.String targetNamespace,
                   Content content,
                   boolean isScopeGlobal)
            throws SchemaException
    Creates an instance of an ComplexType. If the QName is null, the complex type is treated as an anonymous complex type.
    Parameters:
    name - name encapsulating the name of the complex type definition; null if the complex type is anonymous
    targetNamespace - the targetNamespace of the element.
    content - encapsulates the content on the complex type. The content is either a <simpleContent> or <complexContent>. A complex type is derived either by extending or restricting a simpleContent or complexContent.
    isScopeGlobal - boolean that determines if the type can be used by all elements in the schema. Complex type definition that has element as the ancestor are treated as global elements.
    Throws:
    SchemaException - if the content is null
